      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The constant snagging or catching feeling could be related to the feed dogs or how the fabric is being gripped. Both can cause the fabric to bind or bunch up. Another possibility is that the fabric is getting \"stuck\" on the side rails of thePresser foot, especially if it's a brand or model that has a shallow setback or if the longarm foot is over-tightened. This can cause the fabric to ride up and create those puckered lines.",
